0jF\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering auditing in repos**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether the audit repo should be included—well, it seems like there's no harm in that. The EntityManager scans through all the packages, which is fine. I need to consider if auditing requires annotations like @EntityListeners, @CreatedDate, @LastModifiedDate, and @CreatedBy. Should I use Date or Instant for timestamps? Also, I’m curious about how auditing interacts with JSR-310 in Spring Data Commons. There’s a lot to sort through!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering entity management**\\n\\nI need to avoid modifying existing entities directly, except for things like configuration and repository scanning. By adding an `AuditedRecordRepository` as a separate entity, it keeps things cleaner. This approach ensures there’s no effect on the sample user, which seems like a good practice. I'll make sure to implement it this way to maintain the integrity of the existing system while still achieving my goals. This feels like the right decision!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Setting up auditing tests**\\n\\nI'm enabling JpaAuditing and AuditorAware. Existing tests should be fine even if there are no audited entities. If JpaSampleUser isn’t annotated, that’s okay. I need to import some classes for a new entity, including auditing-related classes. I might also need to assert that Instant values are not null.\\n\\nIn my test, I'm checking that an auditing entity listener correctly populates the auditor and timestamps. I’ll ensure certain assertions hold true regarding the state of this entity after saving it. I also contemplate repository methods and their necessity for audit verification.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying CRUD operations**\\n\\nI might consider adding `repository.findById(saved.getId())` after saving for additional assurance, but it seems like CRUD operations are covered. I can assert that the entity is saved successfully. However, there is a potential issue where LastModifiedDate can equal CreatedDate if the update happens in the same millisecond. I need to use isAfterOrEqualTo for that.\\n\\nIt might not guarantee that the modified date has changed but can verify the population of fields. Checking that @CreatedDate remains unchanged could be good; though, I may require a protected constructor for the public API.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_125BoOyANGWWm5l2MPWmapLN|fc_0139d135a36619540169ff3db2037c8193a4b0d7b04db70781", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework.data/spring-data-jpa/2.7.18/src/test/java/org_springframework_data/spring_data_jpa/Spring_data_jpaTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import javax.persistence.Entity;\nimport javax.persistence.EntityManagerFactory;\nimport javax.persistence.EnumType;", "newText": "import javax.persistence.Entity;\nimport javax.persistence.EntityListeners;\nimport javax.persistence.EntityManagerFactory;\nimport javax.persistence.EnumType;"}, {"oldText": "import org.springframework.data.domain.Example;\nimport org.springframework.data.domain.ExampleMatcher;\nimport org.springframework.data.domain.Page;", "newText": "import org.springframework.data.domain.AuditorAware;\nimport org.springframework.data.domain.Example;\nimport org.springframework.data.domain.ExampleMatcher;\nimport org.springframework.data.domain.Page;"}, {"oldText": "import org.springframework.data.jpa.convert.threeten.Jsr310JpaConverters;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.domain.JpaSort;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.domain.Specification;", "newText": "import org.springframework.data.jpa.convert.threeten.Jsr310JpaConverters;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.domain.JpaSort;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.domain.Specification;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.domain.support.AuditingEntityListener;"}, {"oldText": "import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Query;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.config.EnableJpaRepositories;", "newText": "import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Query;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.config.EnableJpaAuditing;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.config.EnableJpaRepositories;"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void domainSortHelpersAndJavaTimeConvertersExposeStablePublicBehavior() {", "newText": "    @Test\n    void auditingEntityListenerPopulatesAuditorAndTimestamps() {\n        try (AnnotationConfigApplicationContext context =\n                new AnnotationConfigApplicationContext(JpaTestConfiguration.class)) {\n            JpaAuditedRecordRepository repository = context.getBean(JpaAuditedRecordRepository.class);\n\n            JpaAuditedRecord saved = repository.saveAndFlush(new JpaAuditedRecord(\"initial\"));\n\n            assertThat(saved.getCreatedBy()).isEqualTo(\"spring-data-jpa-test\");\n            assertThat(saved.getLastModifiedBy()).isEqualTo(\"spring-data-jpa-test\");\n            assertThat(saved.getCreatedAt()).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(saved.getLastModifiedAt()).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(saved.getLastModifiedAt()).isAfterOrEqualTo(saved.getCreatedAt());\n\n            Instant createdAt = saved.getCreatedAt();\n            saved.setDescription(\"updated\");\n\n            JpaAuditedRecord updated = repository.saveAndFlush(saved);\n\n            assertThat(updated.getCreatedAt()).isEqualTo(createdAt);\n            assertThat(updated.getLastModifiedAt()).isAfterOrEqualTo(createdAt);\n            assertThat(updated.getLastModifiedBy()).isEqualTo(\"spring-data-jpa-test\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void domainSortHelpersAndJavaTimeConvertersExposeStablePublicBehavior() {"}, {"oldText": "    @EnableTransactionManagement\n    @EnableJpaRepositories(basePackageClasses = Spring_data_jpaTest.class)\n    public static class JpaTestConfiguration {", "newText": "    @EnableTransactionManagement\n    @EnableJpaAuditing\n    @EnableJpaRepos